
1. EC2LinuxLaunch
Topic: Launching EC2 Linux Instance with a httpd webserver installed on it via bootstrap scripts

PART 1: Launch EC2 Instance with httpd Web Server (Bootstrap)


1. Login to AWS Console
https://console.aws.amazon.com/

2. In the AWS search bar → Type EC2→ Press Enter

3. Click on Launch Instances

4. Under "Name", enter:
cst-R9ST-WebServer-EC2
aps2-mano-WebServer1-EC2

5. Choose Amazon Machine Image (AMI):
Amazon Linux 2 AMI (HVM), Kernel 5.x, SSD Volume Type
(This is Free Tier eligible)

6. Instance Type:
t2.micro (Free Tier eligible)
Leave as default

7. Key Pair (Login)
If you already have one, select it
If not:
• Click Create new key pair
• Key pair name: cst-R9ST-WebKey   aps2-mano-EC2-1
• Key pair type: RSA
• Private key format: .pem OR .ppk
• Choose .ppk if you are using windows machine and choose .pem if you are using macbook. Click Create key pair
